<section class="wide-banner clickable-whole event-banner">
  <div>
    <div>
      NixOS 23.05 <span class="-detailed">released.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="action">
      <a target="_blank" href="[% root %]blog/announcements.html#nixos-23.05">Announcement</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="home-hero">
  <div>
    <div class="blurb">
      <h1>Declarative builds <span>and deployments.</span></h1>
      <p>
        Nix is a tool that takes a unique approach to package management and
        system configuration. Learn how to make reproducible, declarative and
        reliable systems.
      </p>
      <div class="button-tray">
        <a class="button -primary" href="[% root %]download.html">Download</a>
        <a class="button" href="[% root %]learn.html">Get started</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    [% PROCESS demoPreview demo="cover" %]
  </div>
</section>

[% PROCESS demoPane demo="cover" %]

<section id="why-nix" class="home-whynix">
  <div>
    <ul class="whynix">
      <li>
        [% PROCESS svg path="site-styles/assets/gfx-landing-declarative.svg" %]
        <h2>Declaration</h2>
        <p>
          Nix makes it <strong>trivial to share development and build
          environments</strong> for your projects, supporting many programming
          languages and tools, through
          <a href="https://nix.dev/tutorials/first-steps/towards-reproducibility-pinning-nixpkgs">pinning</a>
          and caching.
          If a package works on one machine, it will also work on another.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        [% PROCESS svg path="site-styles/assets/gfx-landing-reproducible.svg" %]
        <h2>Reproducibility</h2>
        <p>
          Nix <strong>builds packages in isolation</strong> from each other to enable
          <a href="https://reproducible-builds.org/">reproducible builds</a>.
          The <a href="https://nixos.wiki/wiki/Binary_Cache">Nix cache</a
          keeps build toolchains available in their exact binary version.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        [% PROCESS svg path="site-styles/assets/gfx-landing-reliable.svg" %]
        <h2>Consistency</h2>
        <p>
          Nix ensures that installing or upgrading one package cannot break
          other packages via consistent package source snapshots named
          <a href="https://nixos.wiki/wiki/Nix_channels">channels</a>.
          That allows you to <strong>roll back to previous versions</strong>,
          and keeps the entire system is in a consistent state during upgrades.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

